title: Volleyball: Pine School wins No. 15
text:

HOBIE HILER / SPECIAL TO TREASURE COAST NEWSPAPERS Master’s Academy’s Halle Morgan (16) spikes the ball during a volleyball match against The Pine School at The Pine School on Thursday in Hobe Sound. Show Caption Previous Next 
Ali Denney had 25 kills, 14 digs and five aces Thursday as Pine School’s volleyball team defeated Master’s Academy 25-8, 25-15, 25-11 in a District 11-2A match at Hobe Sound. 
Annelie Romero added five kills, 10 digs and five aces for Pine School (15-3, 9-2 district). 
Melissa Coolidge had 29 assists and three aces. Niya Adlersberg had six blocks. 
Sasha Chisholm had four kills and two aces for Master’s Academy (2-12, 1-11). 
Rachel St. Mary had three kills and three blocks. Emily Prescott had three kills. 
Pine School plays at 5 p.m. Friday at Morningside Academy. Master’s Academy plays at 5 p.m. Thursday at St. Edward’s. 
Martin County d. Treasure Coast, 25-9, 25-12, 25-6: Mckenzie Gail had five kills, six aces and five digs as the Tigers won their sixth consecutive match. 
Hayley Turner added three kills, seven digs and five aces for Martin County (18-4). Brylee Frank had four digs, three kills and 12 assists. 
Sarah Moehring and Chloe VanHart added four kills apiece. 
Martin County plays South Fork at 6 p.m. Monday. 
South Fork d. Fort Pierce Central, 25-19, 21-25, 25-23, 25-19: Kylee Quigley had 12 kills, 19 digs, nine service points and two aces in the Cobras’ loss to the Bulldogs (16-4) in Fort Pierce. 
Alexis Shipman had 11 kills, three blocks and six digs for Fort Pierce Central (9-8). McKenzie Perslin had 27 assists, nine digs and five service points. 
Valerie Flecha had eight service points and 28 digs. Krista Hoyt had seven service points, three aces and 11 digs. 
Fort Pierce Central hosts Lincoln Park Academy at 6 p.m. Tuesday. 
St. Edward’s d. St. Andrew’s Episcopal 25-7, 25-20, 25-17: Emily Hudson had 30 assists, three kills and three aces as the Pirates won in Fort Pierce. 
Angela Schwerer added 10 kills and Olivia Oriaku had seven kills and 15 service points for St. Edward’s (10-7). 
The Pirates play at 6 p.m. Monday at John Carroll Catholic. 
Brevard HEAT d. Morningside Academy, 23-25, 25-14, 25-23, 25-17: The HEAT won a District 11-2A match in Port St. Lucie. 
Michelle Hetzel had seven kills and 16 digs for Morningside Academy. 
Jordan Mann added eight kills for the Eagles. Amber Robinson finished with 16 assists and three kills. 
Morningside Academy hosts Pine School at 5 p.m. Friday. 
Suncoast d. Port St. Lucie, 25-14, 25-5, 25-16: The Jaguars lost a home match.
